                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well, as a rule AE doesn't hit every time for a couple reasons, first of all you dont run a perfect circle even when everything goes right, theres drift, you really run more of an oval. Due to that, there are times when your song hits at the wrong part of the oval, ergo too much space, and you miss. Thats just another thing you have to time along with your circles.
<br />
 Cap is 4.2, and it takes a goodly amount of AA to get it that high, not to mention gear. In PoV it isn't as much of an issue, but HoH it is, where you need to make bigger circles. And yes for the enchanters out there that don't know, it is an incredibly dangerous way to get xp, I am decent at it, and its a major rush from start to finish. I still die a whole lot more than any other class soloing- However, it takes alot of things to go just right to be successful, low zone pop, great connection, constant attention,right mobs, no casters , no summoners, little to no wanderers once kite is started, and several other things that don't matter to anyone but bards. Example, someone walking up and watching my kite can wipe me if they cast a spell, or bring a group close, due to a microsecond of lag. Doesn't always happen, but has. It may look effortless, but trust me it isn't, and very very few bards do it at high levels since it was nerfed. I have seen exactly one other bard on Tunare do it besides myself since then, and there aren't many places it works, so I think I would have run into a horde of bards doing it at one time or another. Look at EQdiva's boards, a whole lot of folks want to learn it, but very few succeed at it or enjoy it enough to do it on a regular basis. And less since the nerfbat came a'swingin. Sorry for bugging you guys, nice board you have here:)</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.wildcarddesigns.com/images/edsigb.jpg" border="0" />
