                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This is such a happy fun filled thread...
<br />

<br />
Seriously, leave bards be.  There are few enough of them around anyway, and if more people realized how truely awesome they are in groups they would be wanted as much as chant/sham/cleric.  Called for a nerf is as lame as you can get.  It's happened to us enchanters enough, you think you wouldn't want the same upon someone else.
<br />

<br />
So what if a bard can kill 50 db mobs in 15 mins.  The other night I took a Vxed group consisting of a ranger, cleric, warrior, rogue, another enchanter and myself.  We used two charm pets fully hasted and equiped with mage summoned gear we picked up in the bazaar.   We were engaging some of the more difficult (no, not hardest) single group content in the game.  I could NOT land slow on the inc mobs before they hit the ground.  With spell haste + BoR I had something like a 4.6 second cast time.  All the mobs in Vxed are high DB to yellow con mobs (saved named) and they were being dropped in 4-5 seconds... They would get 1-2 attacks in on the warrior.  We did our 50 mobs in Vxed in 15-20 mins.  Guess charm is still broken.  We can kill faster than a AoE/Swarm kiting bard.
<br />

<br />
Necros/Wizards can kite mobs in PoFire for something like 14% AA a kill.  A group in Fire can get something along the lines of 4-6% in this method and I've watched mobs drop in 30 seconds.  There is *almost* NO risk involved in this.  In the group situation, if one person can't get snare to land, someone else will.
<br />

<br />
Wanna nerf bards so bad?  What about the fact that there is NO way they can solo a mob that snares/roots or summons (well, almost.. nearly anything is possible given the right player) Enchanters, however, are the only class capable of soloing many high end named mobs.  I've killed many named in tactics that require a group otherwise.  But if we get unlucky, we are dead.
<br />

<br />
5 plat says that the bard that took "your" camp wouldn't have stood a chance facing that named you were after.  Maybe grouping is too powerful!  We should nerf grouping.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, calling out for nerfing because you are jealous of another classes ability is just lame.  Seriously lame.  It just hurts the entire EQ community in general.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=685971" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://l33tpenguin.50megs.com/arax-sig6.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
