Read what I said again. I said -feign- 17 times, as monks seem to all too often do while trying to figure out what still has aggro on them.  It's a modest exageration,  since I probably don't see them do it more than 6, but it's to drive a point home:
<br />

<br />
When I group with a bard who is pulling, they run out,  mez, pacify, and maybe fade once, and then they're back with a pull.
<br />

<br />
When I group with a monk, they run out, tag, grab a whole roomful of mobs unless sneak splitting worked,  feign, wait,   Stand, Feign again, wait, stand, feign again,  and then usually come back to camp with more mobs than the bard.
<br />

<br />
The fact that bards have a metric ton of pulling tools, all of which are amplified by fade really makes the abject lack of tools available to the "traditional" pulling classes stand out.  
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">FD is slower for splitting, but a whole lot more reliable,</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I really have to question this assertion.  I've never seen fade fail.  I've never HEARD of fade failing.   I've never seen a bard so much as pause and THINK about the possibility of fade failing.  They hit the button, and aggro is gone.   Yes, mobs can re-aggro if the bard is too close, but at least the bard can move away while invis, whereas the monk has to lie there until the mob moves.  Additionally, I see that "Blah has fallen to the ground" message way more often than I see fade fail (which is easy since, as previously asserted, fade does not fail.)  So... how exactly is feign more reliable?  I just don't get it.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">And the reason I mentioned Fade on every pull, is that you claim it as the end all and be all for pulling,</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
