                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well, Yelwen:
<br />

<br />
Frist off, get your facts straight. Post a parse for all to see or move along. 
<br />

<br />
Secondly, even if from 1st mob dying to last mob dying 3 minutes went by, it takes 5 to 10 minutes to gather all 30 mobs and circle around to get them all perfectly bundled till you can START doing DMG to them. And assuming the AE songs hit ALL mobs ALL the time (which they wont, drift, song hitting at wrong spot of circle, missnotes, etc) it prolly takes around 5 mins to drive the mobs low in HPs so they start dying. Thus, in all you are talking about killing 30 mobs in 15 to 20 minutes. Big deal. 
<br />

<br />
Also, AE kiting is EXTREMELY dangerous, and bards who AE die a lot regardless of how good they are at it, sometimes you just die (lag spike, tree or rock on way, mob warping,etc).
<br />

<br />
Lastly, if you are so burned out on envy about what a bard can do that you cannot, my advice is simple enuff, START a bard.
<br />

<br />
That being said, I play both a 65 Enchantress and a 65 Diva, with enchantress being main, which you might have run into in the past, since unfortuntely I believe you play on my server (MT server).
<br />

<br />
When playing my enchantress, Manizeh, I can go to HoH and kill all Human Hall camp, including yellow con nameds if up and the 2 shirnes at entrance in about 10 to 15 minutes, that is 14 mobs if you never soloed HoH camp. Also, I can go to PoFire and eventually clear (again, clear) most of Field 1 mobs with a charmed fire fluffy, and I rarely die with druid buffs on (9s and SoE), if at all. 
<br />

<br />
I havent started toying with solonig Tipt as of yet, but knowing how awesome experience is there when grouping, and being most of the DPS just the pet, think about it  <img src="images/smiles/icon_twisted.gif" alt="icon_twisted.gif" border="0" /> 
