I say, it is not the class fault if the spells are working as intended, it is SoE's lack of imagination that keeps messing things up, and since they find themselves at fault, they are ready to rush into whatever quick fix that needs to be implementing, with ZERO or NO sufficient testing prior to releasing it, once the whines hit the magic number just so they don't have to listen to whinners anymore. 
